The transition strategy of the Haiti Government has three priorities related to solid waste:
* Ensuring the effective and efficient collection/removal of solid waste in MAPAP and main secondary cities;
* Ensuring an adequate treatment/elimination of solid waste in compliance with social and environmental norms;
* Strengthening the legal, institutional, and financial framework at the national and municipal level, including the adoption of a â¢National Plan for Management of Solid Wasteâ¢ by March 2007 and creation of a National Waste Agency (NWA) by September 2007. No mention is made about the intention of energy from waste recovery.
